article.description: Tulane beats North Texas 73-62 in C-USA play
article.headline: Tulane beats North Texas 73-62 in C-USA play
article.linkText: Tulane beats North Texas 73-62 in C-USA play
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- Jonathan Stark scored 20 points and Louis Dabney added 19 to lead Tulane to a 73-62 Conference USA victory against North Texas on Saturday afternoon. Stark made three of the Green Waves five 3-pointers and Dabney added nine rebounds. The score was tied at 27 at the break, but Tulane (9-8, 1-1) opened up the second half with a 9-0 run. The Mean Green climbed within four (54-50) with 9:02 remaining on the clock, but Tulane quickly shut down any hope of a comeback with a 12-3 run to go up 66-53 with 4:11 left to play. T.J. Taylor came off the bench to lead with 19 points on 5-of-10 shooting and finished with four of the Mean Greens five assists. North Texas (9-7, 0-2) has yet to pick up a conference win in its first year as a member of the Conference USA.
